R&D Team,

 

Please join us for our first all-virtual PCS All Hands for Q1FY21. We will host the All Hands twice so you can participate during a time that works for you. As always, we invite all of R&D, including the BUs that aren’t officially included in Products & Cloud Services, since our solutions span multiple BUs. We’d like  everyone to have access to and understand the FY21 PCS key priorities and deliverables to make cross-BU coordination more seamless. 

 

Stay tuned for more information on the agenda, and be assured that we will leave time to take questions over Zoom. Please contact Jackie Landsman if you have any questions on the meeting.

 

We look forward to seeing you – virtually - at our Q1FY21 All Hands!

 

Raghu and Rajiv

events.subject: Tech Talk: Data Labelling for ML using InstaML Loop
events.bodyPreview:
Tech Talks – Office of the CTO!


Join us for this Tech Talk: Data Labelling for ML using InstaML Loop with speaker Steve Liang and Julia Li.

In this talk, we introduce Loop, a data annotation platform to create high quality labelled datasets for

body.content:
Tech Talks – Office of the CTO!

 

 

Join us for this Tech Talk: Data Labelling for ML using InstaML Loop with speaker Steve Liang and Julia Li.

 

In this talk, we introduce Loop, a data annotation platform to create high quality labelled datasets for supervised machine learning. Loop enables rapid experimentation by providing highly customizable annotation interfaces for natural language processing, computer vision, and structured data. By centralizing the data annotation process, Loop significantly reduces the project management overhead by enabling all VMware employees to join a distributed network of human annotators.

 

Integration of upstream data services simplify data access and storage, while downstream integrations with machine learning platforms enables recommendations to annotators. Our current implementation supports tabular and text classification with additional interfaces planned for image recognition and other NLP tasks.

 

Speakers

 

Julia Li is a Staff Engineer in the Globalization Tools Information Experience (GTIX) team. She is a lead developer on VMware Code, Project AVA, and InstaML to develop machine learning models to boost developer productivity.

 

Steve Liang is a Staff Architect at VMware. He leads the InstaML team building common ML services with a focus on applied machine learning and NLP research.
